e":null,"profile_image":"https://res-2.cloudinary.com/hrvj5zvjc/image/upload/q_auto/v1/ghost-blog-images/author-dg-photo.png","location":"Yongin, Korea","website":"https://www.nadaegyun.com","twitter":"@nadaegyun","facebook":"nadaegyun","meta_title":null,"meta_description":null,"coverImageSharp":null,"profileImageSharp":null}],"primary_author":{"slug":"daegyun","url":"https://nadaegyun.herokuapp.com/author/daegyun/","name":"Daegyun Na","bio":"\"The greatest discovery of my generation is that a human being can alter his life by altering his attitudes\"","cover_image":null,"profile_image":"https://res-2.cloudinary.com/hrvj5zvjc/image/upload/q_auto/v1/ghost-blog-images/author-dg-photo.png","location":"Yongin, Korea","website":"https://www.nadaegyun.com","twitter":"@nadaegyun","facebook":"nadaegyun","meta_title":null,"meta_description":null,"coverImageSharp":null,"profileImageSharp":{"base":"author-dg-photo.png","publicURL":"/static/96900429c478476972aa4713e5c60704/author-dg-photo.png","imageMeta":{"width":100,"height":100},"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","aspectRatio":1,"src":"/static/96900429c478476972aa4713e5c60704/3ba9f/author-dg-photo.png","srcSet":"/static/96900429c478476972aa4713e5c60704/7d89d/author-dg-photo.png 28w,\n/static/96900429c478476972aa4713e5c60704/f4091/author-dg-photo.png 55w,\n/static/96900429c478476972aa4713e5c60704/3ba9f/author-dg-photo.png 100w","srcWebp":"/static/96900429c478476972aa4713e5c60704/66016/author-dg-photo.webp","srcSetWebp":"/static/96900429c478476972aa4713e5c60704/59cda/author-dg-photo.webp 28w,\n/static/96900429c478476972aa4713e5c60704/7da75/author-dg-photo.webp 55w,\n/static/96900429c478476972aa4713e5c60704/66016/author-dg-photo.webp 100w","sizes":"(max-width: 100px) 100vw, 100px"}}}},"primary_tag":null,"tags":[{"slug":"hash-visudo","url":"https://nadaegyun.herokuapp.com/404/","name":"#visudo","visibility":"internal","feature_image":null,"description":null,"meta_title":null,"meta_description":null,"featureImageSharp":null},{"slug":"hash-pkexec","url":"https://nadaegyun.herokuapp.com/404/","name":"#pkexec","visibility":"internal","feature_image":null,"description":null,"meta_title":null,"meta_description":null,"featureImageSharp":null},{"slug":"linux","url":"https://nadaegyun.herokuapp.com/tag/linux/","name":"Linux","visibility":"public","feature_image":null,"description":null,"meta_title":null,"meta_description":null,"featureImageSharp":null},{"slug":"hash-sudo","url":"https://nadaegyun.herokuapp.com/404/","name":"#sudo","visibility":"internal","feature_image":null,"description":null,"meta_title":null,"meta_description":null,"featureImageSharp":null},{"slug":"tips","url":"https://nadaegyun.herokuapp.com/tag/tips/","name":"TIPS","visibility":"public","feature_image":null,"description":null,"meta_title":null,"meta_description":null,"featureImageSharp":null}],"plaintext":"Super user do called sudo in Linux and macOS  is to run commands or programs as\nroot user. When you use sudo in terminal it is required to enter password every\ntime that I really don't like because it is not convenient, but there could be a\nreason  why password is rquired to enter in sudo every time. (maybe security\nreason..I guess)\n\nLinux\n 1. open terminal\n\n2.\tedit the /etc/sudoers file by typing visudo command\n\nsudo visudo\n\n\n\n3.\tappend the following entry to run all commands without a password \n\n4.\treboot\n\nreboot\n\nmacOS\nThis for Linux also works in macOS as well.\n\n 1. open terminal\n\n2.\tedit the /etc/sudoers file by typing visudo command\n\nsudo visudo\n\n3.\tappend the following entry to run all commands without a password\n\nuser ID ALL=(ALL) NOPASSSD:ALL\n\n4.\treboot\n\nreboot\n\nTrouble shooting\n> In case that sudo cannot be executed caused by syntax error, use pkexec. pkexec \nallows an authorized user to execute program as another user.\n 1. execute pkexec to run visudo as another user to correct syntax error\n\npkexec visudo\n\n2. find and fix error","html":"<p>Super user do called <strong>sudo</strong> in Linux and macOS  is to run commands or programs as root user. When you use sudo in terminal it is required to enter password every time that I really don't like because it is not convenient, but there could be a reason  why password is rquired to enter in sudo every time. (maybe security reason..I guess)</p><h3 id=\"linux\">Linux</h3><ol><li>open terminal</li></ol><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://digitalpress.fra1.cdn.digitaloceanspaces.com/p3gdkut/2021/02/Screenshot-from-2021-01-30-19-56-24-1.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt></figure><p>2.\tedit the /etc/sudoers file by typing visudo command</p><pre><code>sudo visudo</code></pre><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://digitalpress.fra1.cdn.digitaloceanspaces.com/p3gdkut/2021/02/Screenshot-from-2021-01-30-18-27-28-1.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt></figure><p></p><p>3.\tappend the following entry to run all commands without a password </p><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://digitalpress.fra1.cdn.digitaloceanspaces.com/p3gdkut/2021/02/Screenshot-from-2021-01-30-18-29-11-2.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt></figure><p>4.\treboot</p><pre><code>reboot</code></pre><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://digitalpress.fra1.cdn.digitaloceanspaces.com/p3gdkut/2021/02/Screenshot-from-2021-01-30-18-29-35-2.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt></figure><h3 id=\"macos\">macOS</h3><p>This for Linux also works in macOS as well.</p><ol><li>open terminal</li></ol><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://digitalpress.fra1.cdn.digitaloceanspaces.com/p3gdkut/2021/02/Screen-Shot-2021-01-30-at-6.35.04-PM-2.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt></figure><p>2.\tedit the /etc/sudoers file by typing visudo command</p><pre><code>sudo visudo</code></pre><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://digitalpress.fra1.cdn.digitaloceanspaces.com/p3gdkut/2021/02/Screen-Shot-2021-01-30-at-6.35.21-PM-2.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt></figure><p>3.\tappend the following entry to run all commands without a password</p><pre><code>user ID ALL=(ALL) NOPASSSD:ALL</code></pre><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://digitalpress.fra1.cdn.digitaloceanspaces.com/p3gdkut/2021/02/Screen-Shot-2021-01-30-at-6.35.35-PM-3.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt></figure><p>4.\treboot</p><pre><code>reboot</code></pre><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://digitalpress.fra1.cdn.digitaloceanspaces.com/p3gdkut/2021/02/Screen-Shot-2021-01-30-at-6.36.09-PM-3.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt></figure><h2 id=\"trouble-shooting\">Trouble shooting</h2><blockquote>In case that sudo cannot be executed caused by syntax error, use pkexec. <em><strong>pkexec</strong></em> allows an authorized user to execute program as another user.</blockquote><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://digitalpress.fra1.cdn.digitaloceanspaces.com/p3gdkut/2021/02/Screenshot-from-2021-01-30-18-43-14.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt></figure><ol><li>execute pkexec to run visudo as another user to correct syntax error</li></ol><pre><code>pkexec visudo</code></pre><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://digitalpress.fra1.cdn.digitaloceanspaces.com/p3gdkut/2021/02/Screenshot-from-2021-01-30-18-46-19-2-1.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt></figure><p>2. find and fix error</p><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://digitalpress.fra1.cdn.digitaloceanspaces.com/p3gdkut/2021/02/Screenshot-from-2021-01-30-18-44-08-1-1.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt></figure>","url":"https://nadaegyun.herokuapp.com/sudo-wo-password/","canonical_url":"https://www.nadaegyun.com/sudo-wo-password/","uuid":"360f279f-f2c8-4d83-b417-969510c849ce","codeinjection_foot":null,"codeinjection_head":null,"codeinjection_styles":null,"comment_id":"60150e1f5bcfef0001d3fdc2","reading_time":2,"send_email_when_published":false,"email_subject":null,"childHtmlRehype":{"html":"<p>Super user do called <strong>sudo</strong> in Linux and macOS  is to run commands or programs as root user. When you use sudo in terminal it is required to enter password every time that I really don't like because it is not convenient, but there could be a reason  why password is rquired to enter in sudo every time. (maybe security reason..I guess)</p><h3 id=\"linux\">Linux</h3><ol><li>open terminal</li></ol><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://digitalpress.fra1.cdn.digitaloceanspaces.com/p3gdkut/2021/02/Screenshot-from-2021-01-30-19-56-24-1.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt=\"\"></figure><p>2.\tedit the /etc/sudoers file by typing visudo command</p><div class=\"kg-card kg-code-card gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">sudo visudo</code></pre></div><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://digitalpress.fra1.cdn.digitaloceanspaces.com/p3gdkut/2021/02/Screenshot-from-2021-01-30-18-27-28-1.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt=\"\"></figure><p></p><p>3.\tappend the following entry to run all commands without a password </p><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://digitalpress.fra1.cdn.digitaloceanspaces.com/p3gdkut/2021/02/Screenshot-from-2021-01-30-18-29-11-2.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt=\"\"></figure><p>4.\treboot</p><div class=\"kg-card kg-code-card gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">reboot</code></pre></div><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://digitalpress.fra1.cdn.digitaloceanspaces.com/p3gdkut/2021/02/Screenshot-from-2021-01-30-18-29-35-2.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt=\"\"></figure><h3 id=\"macos\">macOS</h3><p>This for Linux also works in macOS as well.</p><ol><li>open terminal</li></ol><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://digitalpress.fra1.cdn.digitaloceanspaces.com/p3gdkut/2021/02/Screen-Shot-2021-01-30-at-6.35.04-PM-2.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt=\"\"></figure><p>2.\tedit the /etc/sudoers file by typing visudo command</p><div class=\"kg-card kg-code-card gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">sudo visudo</code></pre></div><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://digitalpress.fra1.cdn.digitaloceanspaces.com/p3gdkut/2021/02/Screen-Shot-2021-01-30-at-6.35.21-PM-2.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt=\"\"></figure><p>3.\tappend the following entry to run all commands without a password</p><div class=\"kg-card kg-code-card gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">user ID ALL=(ALL) NOPASSSD:ALL</code></pre></div><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://digitalpress.fra1.cdn.digitaloceanspaces.com/p3gdkut/2021/02/Screen-Shot-2021-01-30-at-6.35.35-PM-3.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt=\"\"></figure><p>4.\treboot</p><div class=\"kg-card kg-code-card gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">reboot</code></pre></div><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://digitalpress.fra1.cdn.digitaloceanspaces.com/p3gdkut/2021/02/Screen-Shot-2021-01-30-at-6.36.09-PM-3.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt=\"\"></figure><h2 id=\"trouble-shooting\">Trouble shooting</h2><blockquote>In case that sudo cannot be executed caused by syntax error, use pkexec. <em><strong>pkexec</strong></em> allows an authorized user to execute program as another user.</blockquote><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"https://digitalpress.fra1.cdn.digitaloceanspaces.com/p3gdkut/2021/02/Screenshot-from-2021-01-30-18-43-14.png\" class=\"kg-image\" alt=\"\"></figure><ol><li>execute pkexec to run visudo as another user to correct syntax error</li></ol><div class=\"kg-card kg-code-card gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">pkexec visudo</code></pre></div><figure class=\"kg-card kg-image-card\"><img src=\"